<i>Danger is always part of this</i>

236
00:18:42,069 --> 00:18:44,299
- How's she doing?
- Stable.

237
00:18:44,404 --> 00:18:46,235
And her vitals are strong.

238
00:18:46,340 --> 00:18:49,241
Blood panels show no irradiation.
Good.

239
00:18:49,343 --> 00:18:52,904
- You'll step up this protocol-
- Every four hours, yes.

240
00:18:53,013 --> 00:18:54,913
We know what we're doing.

241
00:18:55,015 --> 00:18:57,916
- Another day of observation, and you're all clear.
<i>- [ Door Opens ]

242
00:18:58,018 --> 00:18:59,849
<i>[ Cart Squeaking, Rattling ]

243
00:19:03,390 --> 00:19:06,757
She's allergic to orchids.
Put the sunflowers by her bed.

244
00:19:06,860 --> 00:19:08,828
<i>They're her favorites</i>

245
00:19:17,971 --> 00:19:20,098
<i>[ Door Closes ]

246
00:19:26,213 --> 00:19:28,113
<i>Well, Victor</i>

247
00:19:28,215 --> 00:19:30,649
the bank would like
to congratulate you...

248
00:19:30,751 --> 00:19:33,015
<i>on the fastest free-fall</i>
<i>since the Depression</i>

249
00:19:33,120 --> 00:19:36,681
- We can't even give your stock away.
- Ned, I can turn this around.

250
00:19:36,790 --> 00:19:39,281
You're going to have to, Victor,
or we pull out.

251
00:19:42,229 --> 00:19:45,130
- You have a week.
- You're enjoying this, aren't you, Ned?

252
00:19:49,569 --> 00:19:51,537
One week.

253
00:20:19,600 --> 00:20:22,091
<i>Whoa, whoa, whoa</i>
<i>Where do we think we're going?</i>

254
00:20:22,202 --> 00:20:26,195
I don't know if <i>we've</i> noticed, but the sickest
runs this side of the Alps are right outside.

255
00:20:26,306 --> 00:20:30,333
Yeah, I've noticed. But there are rules here.
You can't leave until we-

256
00:20:30,443 --> 00:20:33,276
Until we've finished the tests. I know.
I've never been good with rules.

257
00:20:33,380 --> 00:20:35,940
You let me know
how those come out.

258
00:20:36,049 --> 00:20:39,143
- Do you wanna help me with the zipper?
- This is not a ski resort.

259
00:20:40,253 --> 00:20:41,982
Not yet.

260
00:20:42,088 --> 00:20:44,682
Luckily, Grandma still sends care packages.
It's amazing.

261
00:20:44,791 --> 00:20:47,282
- For an 80-year-old woman, you'd be surpri-
- You are trouble.

262
00:20:47,394 --> 00:20:49,794
<i>Mmm "Trouble"is my middle name</i>

263
00:20:49,896 --> 00:20:52,057
- Oh, you're hot.
- Why, thank you. So are you.

264
00:20:52,165 --> 00:20:55,157
- And I'm not afraid to cry.
- No, I mean you feel a little feverish.

265
00:20:55,268 --> 00:20:58,396
I've never felt better in my life.
My God, you smell good.

266
00:20:58,505 --> 00:21:00,973
- When do you get off work?
- 4:00, but l-

267
00:21:01,074 --> 00:21:04,168
Tell you what. You meet me at 4:01
at the top of the mountain.

268
00:21:04,277 --> 00:21:06,677
That'll give you
a minute to freshen up.

269
00:21:06,780 --> 00:21:08,975
This is yours. That's mine.

270
00:21:09,082 --> 00:21:11,209
[ Whispers ]
Nurses!

271
00:21:13,620 --> 00:21:15,383
<i>[ Monitor Beeping ]

272
00:21:16,756 --> 00:21:18,883
<i>How long was I out?</i>

273
00:21:18,992 --> 00:21:20,892
Hey. Three days.

274
00:21:20,994 --> 00:21:23,690
I was worried about you.
How are you feeling?

275
00:21:23,797 --> 00:21:25,697
Solid.

276
00:21:25,799 --> 00:21:29,758
Uh, it was a close one, though, huh?
What was that about?

277
00:21:29,869 --> 00:21:32,702
I don't know.

278
00:21:32,806 --> 00:21:34,706
I really don't know.

279
00:21:34,808 --> 00:21:38,938
I've been going over the figures again and again,
and they all add up.

280
00:21:39,045 --> 00:21:41,946
I just don't understand.
Maybe I should've aborted-

281
00:21:42,048 --> 00:21:45,176
Reed, it was a freak of nature.
You couldn't have possibly predicted it.

282
00:21:45,285 --> 00:21:48,516
- Let it go.
- [ Exhales ]

283
00:21:48,621 --> 00:21:51,419
You know, you live through
something like this...

284
00:21:51,524 --> 00:21:53,856
<i>it really makes you appreciate</i>
<i>having the right woman in your life</i>

285
00:21:53,960 --> 00:21:58,294
- Yeah, you and Debbie are perfect.
- I'm not talking about Debbie.

286
00:22:00,166 --> 00:22:02,532
What? Come on.

287
00:22:02,635 --> 00:22:04,432
She's got a good thing with Victor.

288
00:22:04,537 --> 00:22:08,132
- He's smart, he's powerful, he's successful-
- Maybe you should date him then.

289
00:22:08,241 --> 00:22:12,143
Ben, she ended up
with the right guy.

290
00:22:12,245 --> 00:22:15,043
Things worked out for the best.

291
00:22:17,684 --> 00:22:20,312
Do I have to do everything myself?

292
00:22:20,420 --> 00:22:22,888
<i>##[ Rock ]

293
00:22:26,092 --> 00:22:28,151
<i>##[ Man Singing ]

294
00:22:41,441 --> 00:22:44,342
You should stay to the right.
The left might give you trouble.

295
00:22:44,444 --> 00:22:47,345
- I think we should drop, like, 10 more feet.
- Good.

296
00:22:47,447 --> 00:22:49,745
Last one down
springs for room service!

297
00:22:50,850 --> 00:22:52,613
Whoo-hoo!

298
00:22:52,719 --> 00:22:54,448
<i>##[ Continues ]

299
00:22:57,557 --> 00:22:59,457
My future wife!

300
00:23:05,632 --> 00:23:07,463
Whoo-hoo!

301
00:23:20,146 --> 00:23:22,774
Whoo!

302
00:23:25,985 --> 00:23:27,680
You're losing!

303
00:23:27,787 --> 00:23:30,255
All right, no more kid stuff.

304
00:23:31,324 --> 00:23:33,554
Check this out!

305
00:23:36,062 --> 00:23:39,520
<i>##[ Continues ]

306
00:23:39,632 --> 00:23:43,363
- You're on fire!
- Thanks! You're pretty good too!

307
00:23:43,469 --> 00:23:46,438
No! You're on <i>fire!</i> Look!

308
00:23:46,539 --> 00:23:49,030
<i>##[ Continues ]

309
00:23:49,142 --> 00:23:51,406
- Whoa!
- Whoa!

310
00:23:54,781 --> 00:23:56,908
[ Grunting ]

311
00:23:58,117 --> 00:24:00,915
[ Screams ]

312
00:24:02,255 --> 00:24:04,655
[ Screaming Continues ]

313
00:24:04,757 --> 00:24:07,885
Whoa-ohh!

314
00:24:20,106 --> 00:24:22,700
Care to join me?

315
00:24:30,116 --> 00:24:32,778
I can only stay for one drink.
I have to meet Victor.

316
00:24:32,885 --> 00:24:35,581
Oh. Wouldn't want
to keep Vic waiting.

317
00:24:35,688 --> 00:24:37,849
Reed, what are you doing here?

318
00:24:37,957 --> 00:24:40,892
I thought-

319
00:24:42,161 --> 00:24:45,062
<i>Great!</i>
<i>Uh, maybe you can join us</i>

320
00:24:45,164 --> 00:24:47,689
<i>- How's the IPO now?</i>
- It's fallen.

321
00:24:47,800 --> 00:24:50,735
We're looking at low 20s.
It's a good number, considering the fallout from-

322
00:24:50,837 --> 00:24:52,805
From Reed's disaster?

323
00:24:52,905 --> 00:24:57,239
<i>Get me on the am shows,</i>
<i>Larry King, cover of the</i> Journal.

324
00:24:57,343 --> 00:25:00,642
Gonna have to do something
about this scar.

325
00:25:00,747 --> 00:25:04,410
Make sure they only shoot me
from my left side.

326
00:25:04,517 --> 00:25:07,418
Actually, uh, the scar's tracking well.

327
00:25:07,520 --> 00:25:09,920
People seem to think
it humanizes you.

328
00:25:10,023 --> 00:25:12,992
[ Chuckles ]
And that's a good thing?

329
00:25:15,261 --> 00:25:16,990
[ Gasps, Sighs ]

330
00:25:17,096 --> 00:25:19,087
Maybe you should get some rest.

331
00:25:19,198 --> 00:25:21,098
Later.

332
00:25:21,200 --> 00:25:23,600
First I have some unfinished business.

333
00:25:23,703 --> 00:25:26,001
A deal that needs closing.

334
00:25:26,105 --> 00:25:28,665
Sir, I have always wondered-
Why Sue?

335
00:25:28,775 --> 00:25:31,676
<i>You could have any other woman</i>
<i>in the world</i>

336
00:25:31,778 --> 00:25:35,339
That's why. Because I could
have any other woman.

337
00:25:35,448 --> 00:25:39,111
- [ Laughing ]
- No, let me tell the story! Let me tell the story!

338
00:25:39,218 --> 00:25:41,345
- [ Gurgling ]
- Oh-

339
00:25:41,454 --> 00:25:43,354
[ Gasps ]

340
00:25:43,456 --> 00:25:45,583
<i>- [ Gurgling Continues ]
- Wow.

341
00:25:45,692 --> 00:25:48,160
<i>- [ Ben Exhales ]
- You all right?

342
00:25:48,261 --> 00:25:50,195
[ Sighs ]
Bad shrimp.

343
00:25:50,296 --> 00:25:52,457
I think I'd better go lie down.

344
00:25:52,565 --> 00:25:54,192
Excuse me.

345
00:25:55,334 --> 00:25:57,029
[ Groans ]
Oh, God.

346
00:25:57,136 --> 00:25:59,104
<i>[ Ben Groans, Chuckles ]

347
00:25:59,205 --> 00:26:01,139
[ Sighs ]

348
00:26:02,175 --> 00:26:03,802
[ Chuckles ]

349
00:26:13,286 --> 00:26:15,345
<i>[ Reed ]
<i>So, are you feeling better?</i>

350
00:26:15,455 --> 00:26:17,855
Yes. Thank you.

351
00:26:17,957 --> 00:26:20,357
Good.

352
00:26:20,460 --> 00:26:23,554
That's, uh, good.

353
00:26:26,165 --> 00:26:28,133
You always had a way with words.

354
00:26:32,405 --> 00:26:34,305
Uh-Wow.

355
00:26:34,407 --> 00:26:37,672
I should be going, 'cause, uh...

356
00:26:37,777 --> 00:26:39,677
I have to meet Victor.

357
00:26:39,779 --> 00:26:42,407
I'm really happy for you and Victor.

358
00:26:42,515 --> 00:26:44,915
You're really happy
for me and Victor?

359
00:26:45,017 --> 00:26:48,680
I can tell you guys are enjoying
what was the best part of our relationship.

360
00:26:48,788 --> 00:26:50,881
- Which was?
- Passion.

361
00:26:52,492 --> 00:26:54,756
For science.

362
00:26:54,861 --> 00:26:57,557
You are such a dork, Reed.

363
00:26:57,663 --> 00:27:01,190
You never got it,
and you never will.

364
00:27:01,300 --> 00:27:03,996
- What did I say?
- Unless it's explained to you in quantum physics.

365
00:27:04,103 --> 00:27:06,663
I just wanted
to let you know that I was-

366
00:27:06,773 --> 00:27:09,708
It's been two years, and all you can say
is you're happy for me and some other guy?

367
00:27:09,809 --> 00:27:12,107
<i>Victor may be a lot of things</i>

368
00:27:12,211 --> 00:27:15,112
<i>but at least he's not afraid</i>
<i>to fight for what he wants</i>

369
00:27:15,214 --> 00:27:18,445
It's nice to be wanted
sometimes, Reed...

370
00:27:20,219 --> 00:27:23,620
to be seen and heard.

371
00:27:25,324 --> 00:27:27,292
Look at me.

372
00:27:28,828 --> 00:27:30,728
I can't.

373
00:27:30,830 --> 00:27:33,924
- What do you mean, you can't? Look at me!
- Sue, look at your hands.

374
00:27:34,033 --> 00:27:35,762
[ Gasps ]

375
00:27:37,637 --> 00:27:39,867
[ Gasps ]

376
00:27:54,253 --> 00:27:56,153
Hey! You guys-

377
00:27:56,255 --> 00:27:59,622
Hey. You are never gonna believe
what just happened to me.

378
00:27:59,725 --> 00:28:01,818
What?

379
00:28:01,928 --> 00:28:04,726
Oh. Well, I can explain this.

380
00:28:21,814 --> 00:28:23,782
[ Crackling ]

381
00:28:26,252 --> 00:28:29,221
[ Grunting, Exhaling ]

382
00:28:32,058 --> 00:28:34,959
It has to be the cloud.
It's fundamentally altered our D.N.A.

383
00:28:35,061 --> 00:28:36,961
Let's not jump to conclusions.

384
00:28:37,063 --> 00:28:39,861
We need a massive amount of evidence
before making that leap.

385
00:28:39,966 --> 00:28:41,957
<i>Whoa! Guys, look</i>

386
00:28:45,304 --> 00:28:48,432
<i>[ Fingers Snap ]

387
00:28:51,844 --> 00:28:55,336
Now, picture that, but <i>everywhere!</i>

388
00:28:57,083 --> 00:28:58,983
It was <i>everywhere!</i>

389
00:28:59,085 --> 00:29:01,815
What?

390
00:29:01,921 --> 00:29:04,822
The cloud has fundamentally
altered our D.N.A.

391
00:29:04,924 --> 00:29:07,290
[ Cackles ]
Cool!

392
00:29:07,393 --> 00:29:10,487
- And you know what, guys? I think I was flying.
- We need to find Ben.

393
00:29:10,596 --> 00:29:13,793
- [ Groaning, Screaming ]
<i>- [ Monitors Beeping ]

394
00:29:13,900 --> 00:29:17,461
- [ Heart Beating Rapidly ]
<i>- [ Ben Roaring ]

395
00:29:17,570 --> 00:29:19,470
I said cut it out, Johnny.

396
00:29:19,572 --> 00:29:21,631
- Still getting the hang of it.
- Hey, Ben! It's Reed!

397
00:29:21,741 --> 00:29:23,868
- Stop.
- All right.

398
00:29:23,976 --> 00:29:25,534
- All right?
- Yes!

399
00:29:25,645 --> 00:29:27,738
- God! What's wrong with you?
- God! What?

400
00:29:27,847 --> 00:29:31,010
- Sue, do you know the code?
- [ Roaring, Groaning ]

401
00:29:37,323 --> 00:29:39,018
Hey, Ben! Open up!

402
00:29:39,125 --> 00:29:42,652
- You all right, Ben?
- Hey, does somebody have keys to these doors?

403
00:29:42,762 --> 00:29:44,662
<i>[Johnny ]
<i>Anybody?</i>

404
00:29:44,764 --> 00:29:47,198
<i>Just break the glass</i>
<i>It can't be that thick</i>

405
00:29:47,300 --> 00:29:49,734
<i>[ Lock Pad Beeping ]

406
00:30:22,068 --> 00:30:24,366
[ Beeps ]

407
00:30:30,576 --> 00:30:32,305
That's gross.

408
00:30:32,411 --> 00:30:34,538
<i>[ Thudding, Crashing ]

409
00:30:34,647 --> 00:30:37,309
<i>[ Alarm Beeping ]

410
00:30:37,416 --> 00:30:39,350
<i>[ Reed ]
<i>Ben?</i>

411
00:30:40,386 --> 00:30:42,513
Look! Look, look, look, look!

412
00:30:44,223 --> 00:30:46,657
What is that thing?

413
00:30:49,362 --> 00:30:52,160
<i>What's going on?</i>
<i>What happened in here?</i>

414
00:30:52,264 --> 00:30:55,665
- Are you feeling all right?
- I'm fine. Just a few scrapes, that's all.

415
00:30:55,768 --> 00:31:00,501
<i>Ben did this He's had some kind of</i>
<i>reaction to exposure from the cloud</i>

416
00:31:00,606 --> 00:31:03,097
<i>We all have, um, different symptoms</i>

417
00:31:03,209 --> 00:31:05,109
Symptoms?

418
00:31:05,211 --> 00:31:08,339
- Victor, um, I should have-
- Just find him.

419
00:31:10,216 --> 00:31:13,185
Anybody got any ideas
where the big guy's going?

420
00:31:15,521 --> 00:31:18,490
<i>[ Reed Sighs ]
<i>He's going home</i>

421
00:31:27,299 --> 00:31:30,268
<i>[ Train Passing Overhead ]

422
00:31:42,948 --> 00:31:45,917
- [ Men Laughing, Chattering ]
- ## [ R&B ]

423
00:31:49,955 --> 00:31:52,856
<i>[ Glass Shatters ]

424
00:31:55,394 --> 00:31:58,989
- [ Dial Tone ]
- Oh, you gotta be kiddin' me.

425
00:31:59,098 --> 00:32:01,862
[ Grunting ]

426
00:32:01,967 --> 00:32:05,926
- [ Beep Tones Overlapping ]
- [ Growls ]

427
00:32:07,306 --> 00:32:10,139
Little buttons! Hello, Operator?

428
00:32:10,242 --> 00:32:12,972
<i>[ Line Rings, Clicks ]

429
00:32:13,079 --> 00:32:16,776
<i>- [ Woman ] Hello?</i>
- Debs? It's me.

430
00:32:16,882 --> 00:32:20,511
Ben? Are you all right?
You sound a little different.

431
00:32:20,619 --> 00:32:23,520
- Uh, listen, I need you to come out front.
- Out front?

432
00:32:23,622 --> 00:32:26,489
- You're home, baby?
<i>- [ Sarcastic Chuckle ]

433
00:32:26,592 --> 00:32:29,561
- Yeah.
- [ Laughs ]

434
00:32:29,662 --> 00:32:32,358
I got a surprise for you.

435
00:32:32,465 --> 00:32:34,558
<i>[ Laughs ]

436
00:32:34,667 --> 00:32:38,501
Yeah, I got a little one for you too.

437
00:32:40,773 --> 00:32:42,741
<i>Ben?</i>

438
00:32:45,277 --> 00:32:47,245
Where are you?

439
00:32:47,346 --> 00:32:49,246
I'm over here.

440
00:32:49,348 --> 00:32:52,681
Don't come any closer for a sec, okay?

441
00:32:52,785 --> 00:32:56,050
<i>It's gonna-</i>
<i>It's gonna be a bit of a shock</i>

442
00:32:56,155 --> 00:32:58,350
Honey, what's going on?

443
00:32:58,457 --> 00:33:00,823
Debs...

444
00:33:00,926 --> 00:33:03,918
remember w-when we used to say...

445
00:33:04,029 --> 00:33:06,759
together forever,
no matter what?

446
00:33:06,866 --> 00:33:09,266
Yeah?

447
00:33:11,570 --> 00:33:13,265
Baby, you're scaring me.

448
00:33:26,986 --> 00:33:30,046
- Oh, my God.
- Deb.

449
00:33:30,156 --> 00:33:33,091
It's me. It's still me.
It was the accident.

450
00:33:33,192 --> 00:33:35,126
- Let me explain.
- No! Don't touch me!

451
00:33:35,227 --> 00:33:38,060
- Debs!
- [ Horn Honks ]

452
00:33:38,164 --> 00:33:40,291
<i>[ Cab Driver ]
<i>What are you doin', lady?</i>

453
00:33:42,368 --> 00:33:44,165
<i>Hey! I'm callin'the police!</i>

454
00:33:44,270 --> 00:33:45,828
<i>[ Woman ]
<i>Everybody all right?</i>

455
00:33:45,938 --> 00:33:48,839
<i>- [ Man ] I saw him! It's that guy over there!</i>
<i>- [ Dog Barking ]

456
00:33:48,941 --> 00:33:51,432
<i>[ Man ]
<i>What the hell's going on out there?</i>

457
00:34:12,598 --> 00:34:16,090
[ Grumbling ]

458
00:34:16,202 --> 00:34:21,105
Oh, yeah, Ben.
A few days in space. It'll be great.

459
00:34:21,207 --> 00:34:24,370
What's the worst that could happen?

460
00:34:27,313 --> 00:34:29,213
Hey, little guy.

461
00:34:29,315 --> 00:34:31,681
[ Chuckles ]
You're not afraid of me, are ya?

462
00:34:31,784 --> 00:34:34,184
[ Cooing ]

463
00:34:37,590 --> 00:34:39,888
[ Grumbles ]
Perfect.

464
00:34:41,493 --> 00:34:43,461
Thanks.

465
00:34:46,632 --> 00:34:49,032
[ Muttering ]

466
00:34:55,307 --> 00:34:58,174
<i>- [ Water Splashes ]
- Hey!

467
00:34:58,277 --> 00:35:02,611
- [ Gasps ]
- You think you got problems?
