468
00:35:02,715 --> 00:35:05,479
Huh. How bad could it be, right?

469
00:35:05,584 --> 00:35:07,711
- I don't think you-
- [ Muttering Continues ]

470
00:35:07,820 --> 00:35:11,688
[ Sighs ]
Okay, pal, take it easy.

471
00:35:11,790 --> 00:35:15,658
No, no, no. Don't go out there.
I said stop, you fruitcake!

472
00:35:15,761 --> 00:35:18,730
No, no, no. Come closer.

473
00:35:18,831 --> 00:35:20,924
That's further! Come closer!

474
00:35:21,033 --> 00:35:23,763
I said stop! No, no, no!

475
00:35:23,869 --> 00:35:26,167
Whoa!
[ Grunting ]

476
00:35:26,272 --> 00:35:28,103
<i>[ Ben ]
<i>Feet!</i>

477
00:35:33,612 --> 00:35:35,170
[ Grunts ]

478
00:35:35,281 --> 00:35:37,010
<i>[ Horn Honking ]

479
00:35:38,651 --> 00:35:41,211
Whoa!

480
00:35:46,358 --> 00:35:48,918
- [ Shouting, Chattering ]
- Come here!

481
00:35:59,238 --> 00:36:02,264
[ Horns Honking ]

482
00:36:11,650 --> 00:36:14,312
- [ Shouting, Chattering ]
- All right.

483
00:36:14,420 --> 00:36:16,945
Calm down.

484
00:36:17,056 --> 00:36:19,422
You wanna be scared?
[ Shouts ] Fine!

485
00:36:19,525 --> 00:36:22,494
[ Screams ]

486
00:36:22,594 --> 00:36:24,585
- [ Groaning ]
- [ Coughing ]

487
00:36:28,767 --> 00:36:32,225
- Give me a couple tow trucks.
- Get back! Get back!

488
00:36:32,338 --> 00:36:35,569
<i>Get back in your vehicles!</i>
<i>We'll tell you when you can go!</i>

489
00:36:35,674 --> 00:36:38,472
- What are we gonna do now?
- We're not gonna get past these guys.

490
00:36:38,577 --> 00:36:40,477
But you could.

491
00:36:40,579 --> 00:36:42,274
[ Grunts ]

492
00:36:44,950 --> 00:36:47,350
Sorry about the truck, pal.
Come on.

493
00:36:47,453 --> 00:36:51,321
<i>A little help here</i>
<i>You wanna hit the button, sir?</i>

494
00:36:51,423 --> 00:36:53,448
- Stuck.
- [ Grumbles ]

495
00:36:53,559 --> 00:36:56,619
Sue, your clothes. Lose them.

496
00:36:56,729 --> 00:36:58,287
Oh. Right.

497
00:36:58,397 --> 00:37:00,661
This is so wrong.

498
00:37:04,703 --> 00:37:06,796
- [ Gasps ]
<i>- [ Sue ] What?</i>

499
00:37:06,905 --> 00:37:08,702
[ Gasps ]
Oh!

500
00:37:08,807 --> 00:37:11,275
- Wow. You've been working out.
- Shut up!

501
00:37:13,312 --> 00:37:16,110
All right.
[ Grunting ]

502
00:37:17,916 --> 00:37:20,180
All right, freeze!

503
00:37:21,220 --> 00:37:22,949
Now, just, uh-

504
00:37:23,055 --> 00:37:25,683
just put the man
in the seat down!

505
00:37:26,992 --> 00:37:28,960
Do it!

506
00:37:33,232 --> 00:37:36,690
Any more great ideas? Why don't <i>you</i> strip
down and have 100 people stare at you?

507
00:37:36,802 --> 00:37:38,702
<i>- Sue</i>
<i>- What?</i>

508
00:37:40,072 --> 00:37:43,132
Oh. Hmph!

509
00:37:43,242 --> 00:37:45,802
I'm gonna need therapy.

510
00:37:46,912 --> 00:37:49,380
Come on.
Let's get out of here.

511
00:37:51,350 --> 00:37:54,012
<i>- Excuse me Coming through</i>
- [ Gasping, Shouting ]

512
00:37:57,489 --> 00:38:01,186
<i>Right now, uh,</i>
<i>just back away from him</i>

513
00:38:02,694 --> 00:38:04,525
<i>And, uh, I want you</i>

514
00:38:04,630 --> 00:38:07,030
<i>to put your hands</i>
<i>on your head right-</i>

515
00:38:10,102 --> 00:38:11,899
[ Horn Blasting, Siren Wailing ]

516
00:38:13,972 --> 00:38:15,564
954 approaching scene.

517
00:38:15,674 --> 00:38:18,438
- I still can't believe you made me do that.
- We got through, didn't we?

518
00:38:18,544 --> 00:38:20,444
Just find Ben.

519
00:38:20,546 --> 00:38:23,947
<i>- Stay back of the bridge!</i>
- [ Shouting, Chattering Continues ]

520
00:38:27,286 --> 00:38:29,618
Ben! Ben!

521
00:38:36,161 --> 00:38:39,130
<i>Mom! Mom?</i>

522
00:38:40,399 --> 00:38:42,299
<i>[ Screaming ]

523
00:38:42,401 --> 00:38:45,029
[ Whimpering ]

524
00:38:53,078 --> 00:38:55,876
- Whoa!
- [ Whines ]

525
00:39:14,099 --> 00:39:16,397
[ Groaning ]

526
00:39:24,843 --> 00:39:27,311
- Stay here, okay?
- [ Grunting ]

527
00:39:27,412 --> 00:39:29,346
<i>Coming! Hold on!</i>

528
00:39:31,884 --> 00:39:34,614
- [ Shouting ]
- [ Gasps ]

529
00:39:41,560 --> 00:39:44,154
- [ Grunting ] No, you-
- [ Grunting ]

530
00:39:44,263 --> 00:39:46,458
- [ Whimpers ]
- [ Grunting Continues ]

531
00:39:46,565 --> 00:39:49,432
Don't.

532
00:39:52,137 --> 00:39:54,105
- No!
- [ Screams ]

533
00:39:56,141 --> 00:39:58,666
[ Continues Screaming ]

534
00:40:05,651 --> 00:40:07,118
[ Yells ]

535
00:40:09,555 --> 00:40:11,989
[ Continues Grunting ]

536
00:40:12,090 --> 00:40:15,321
- Hang on!
<i>- [ Onlookers Screaming ]

537
00:40:15,427 --> 00:40:17,452
[ Screaming ]

538
00:40:19,298 --> 00:40:21,198
- Huh?
- I got ya.

539
00:40:27,072 --> 00:40:30,007
[ Yelling ]

540
00:40:46,792 --> 00:40:48,919
[ Exhales ]

541
00:41:00,339 --> 00:41:03,172
<i>[ Officer On Bullhorn ] This is the police!</i>
<i>Get down on the ground!</i>

542
00:41:03,275 --> 00:41:05,106
<i>[ Woman ]
<i>Don't shoot! He's a hero!</i>

543
00:41:05,210 --> 00:41:08,577
<i>- Get down on the ground now!</i>
- [ Shouting, Chattering ]

544
00:41:08,680 --> 00:41:11,911
<i>- [ Onlookers Cheering ]
- Ben!

545
00:41:18,991 --> 00:41:20,686
Whoo-hoo!

546
00:42:26,692 --> 00:42:28,592
I swear to you...

547
00:42:28,694 --> 00:42:31,094
I will do everything in my power...

548
00:42:31,196 --> 00:42:33,596
until there is not a breath left in me-

549
00:42:35,534 --> 00:42:37,968
You're gonna be Ben again.

550
00:42:42,541 --> 00:42:44,338
<i>- How 'bout this guy?</i>
<i>- I don't know</i>

551
00:42:44,443 --> 00:42:47,310
<i>I tell you what-</i>
<i>I never seen nothin'like him before</i>

552
00:42:47,412 --> 00:42:49,209
I told you I felt fine.

553
00:42:50,515 --> 00:42:53,143
Where are your ears?

554
00:42:55,987 --> 00:43:00,549
- There are some folks outside
that want to talk to you.
- We're not going public.

555
00:43:00,659 --> 00:43:03,059
- We're scientists, not celebrities.
- It's too late, son.

556
00:43:04,096 --> 00:43:05,654
Look.

557
00:43:05,764 --> 00:43:08,562
- When a New York Fire Department ladder truck...
- See that?

558
00:43:08,667 --> 00:43:10,567
Became part of the tragedy.

559
00:43:10,669 --> 00:43:13,229
<i>But the rescue itself is not the story</i>

560
00:43:13,338 --> 00:43:15,772
<i>One of the four stretched</i>
<i>to an amazing length-</i>

561
00:43:15,874 --> 00:43:18,707
That's what they're calling you-
the Fantastic Four.

562
00:43:18,810 --> 00:43:21,244
- Cool!
- No, wait! Where are you going?

563
00:43:21,346 --> 00:43:23,075
- I'm gonna go talk to 'em.
- No!

564
00:43:23,181 --> 00:43:26,708
- We should think this through.
- That's great. Brainstorm.

565
00:43:26,818 --> 00:43:30,219
<i>Where is it? Left?</i>

566
00:43:30,322 --> 00:43:33,382
[ Sue ]
Get back here right now! Johnny!

567
00:43:35,193 --> 00:43:38,492
- Settle down!
- [ Reporters Clamoring, Shouting Questions ]

568
00:43:39,998 --> 00:43:42,262
Do you believe this?

569
00:43:42,367 --> 00:43:44,562
- Which one of you is the leader?
- That would be me.

570
00:43:44,669 --> 00:43:47,229
No, seriously.

571
00:43:48,707 --> 00:43:50,698
Okay, son, you're on.

572
00:43:56,681 --> 00:43:58,911
Uh...

573
00:43:59,017 --> 00:44:02,748
during our recent mission
to the Von Doom space station...

574
00:44:04,689 --> 00:44:07,681
we were exposed to
as-yet unidentified radioactive energy.

575
00:44:07,793 --> 00:44:09,852
- What happened on the bridge?
- How can you stretch?

576
00:44:09,961 --> 00:44:12,930
- Is it true you can fly?
- Yeah, I'm working on it. It's actually difficult-

577
00:44:13,031 --> 00:44:16,091
No, actually, we do not know
much more than you do at this point.

578
00:44:16,201 --> 00:44:20,467
Uh, sir, Larry King just canceled.

579
00:44:20,572 --> 00:44:22,972
Apparently there's a bigger story.

580
00:44:23,074 --> 00:44:24,769
NASDAQ was up 9.9-

581
00:44:24,876 --> 00:44:27,640
Bravest-
Actually, here they come now.

582
00:44:27,746 --> 00:44:30,078
<i>You had to see it</i>
<i>to believe it, folks The man-</i>

583
00:44:30,182 --> 00:44:31,877
named the Fantastic Four-

584
00:44:31,983 --> 00:44:34,884
We will be going directly to our lab
to diagnose our symptoms.

585
00:44:34,986 --> 00:44:36,977
<i>[ Reporter ]
<i>Symptoms? Is this some kind of disease?</i>

586
00:44:37,088 --> 00:44:39,454
No! No, no, no.
It's not a disease.

587
00:44:39,558 --> 00:44:44,154
Symptoms? If having special powers
is a disease, then, yeah, we got it bad.

588
00:44:44,262 --> 00:44:46,389
Excuse me.
That thing doesn't look so fantastic.

589
00:44:46,498 --> 00:44:48,398
Ben Grimm is a genuine American hero.

590
00:44:48,500 --> 00:44:50,968
What he means is,
every team needs a mascot.

591
00:44:51,069 --> 00:44:53,833
- [ Laughing ]
- A new day is dawning.

592
00:44:53,939 --> 00:44:56,737
<i>The day of the Fantastic Four!</i>

593
00:44:56,842 --> 00:44:59,572
[ Clamoring, Shouting Questions ]

594
00:44:59,678 --> 00:45:03,978
Look- Look, we went up to space
to find a way to understand D.N. A... .

595
00:45:04,082 --> 00:45:07,848
<i>Cure disease, save lives</i>

596
00:45:07,953 --> 00:45:12,788
Well, now it's our D.N.A.,
our "disease," our lives on the line.

597
00:45:12,891 --> 00:45:15,018
Thank you.
No more questions.

598
00:45:16,728 --> 00:45:19,094
This is how you turn things around?

599
00:45:19,197 --> 00:45:21,097
These freaks on the front page...

600
00:45:21,199 --> 00:45:23,463
your company's in the obituaries?

601
00:45:23,568 --> 00:45:26,469
- I was planning to use the publicity-
<i>- The board's in agreement</i>

602
00:45:26,571 --> 00:45:29,540
- The bank's lost enough already.
- Wait a minute.

603
00:45:29,641 --> 00:45:31,768
It's too late, Victor.

604
00:45:31,877 --> 00:45:35,540
Do you know how much money
I've invested in this company?

605
00:45:35,647 --> 00:45:38,480
Victor, stop.
This isn't a negotiation.

606
00:45:38,583 --> 00:45:40,983
<i>It's a notification</i>

607
00:45:41,086 --> 00:45:43,054
<i>We're pulling out</i>

608
00:45:57,435 --> 00:45:59,903
<i>[ Crowd Cheering ]

609
00:46:24,763 --> 00:46:27,231
Is all that for you, Dr. Richards?

610
00:46:27,332 --> 00:46:28,856
I'm afraid so.

611
00:46:32,037 --> 00:46:35,234
Come on, Ben. Smile.
They wanna like you, bud. Say hi.

612
00:46:35,340 --> 00:46:37,672
[ All Gasping ]

613
00:46:37,776 --> 00:46:41,007
Uh, don't do drugs!

614
00:46:41,112 --> 00:46:44,013
[ Cheering Resumes ]

615
00:46:49,120 --> 00:46:52,351
- [ Grumbles ]
<i>- [ Bell Dings ]

616
00:46:52,457 --> 00:46:55,620
Welcome back to the Baxter,
Dr. Richards.

617
00:46:55,727 --> 00:46:57,752
I've got the usual for you.

618
00:46:57,862 --> 00:47:01,127
- Good to have you back, sir.
- Thanks, Willie.

619
00:47:03,134 --> 00:47:05,034
We had a tough year.

620
00:47:05,136 --> 00:47:07,934
Yeah, like, nine straight.

621
00:47:10,608 --> 00:47:14,044
<i>- [ Bell Dings ]
<i>- [ Pulleys Creaking ]

622
00:47:14,145 --> 00:47:17,114
<i>[ Thuds ]

623
00:47:17,215 --> 00:47:20,480
<i>[ Creaking Continues, Stops ]

624
00:47:20,585 --> 00:47:23,486
Either we're moving
really fast or not at all.

625
00:47:23,588 --> 00:47:26,421
<i>[ Alarm Buzzes ]

626
00:47:26,524 --> 00:47:28,549
<i>[ Bell Dings ]

627
00:47:28,660 --> 00:47:31,288
<i>[ Doors Slide Open ]

628
00:47:31,396 --> 00:47:33,489
I'll take the stairs.

629
00:47:38,269 --> 00:47:40,237
[ Bell Dings ]

630
00:47:43,041 --> 00:47:45,942
How come Ben can't turn it
on and off like we can?

631
00:47:46,044 --> 00:47:48,808
That's what we're here to find out.

632
00:47:48,913 --> 00:47:53,316
- If it happened to him-
- What? You mean, like, we won't
be able to turn it off either?

633
00:47:53,418 --> 00:47:57,149
- That would save time. Ha!
- You wanna walk around on fire
the rest of your life?

634
00:47:57,255 --> 00:47:59,849
- Is that a trick question?
- Grow up.

635
00:47:59,958 --> 00:48:02,654
Come on. Am I the only guy
who thinks this is cool?

636
00:48:02,761 --> 00:48:06,663
We should stay here until we can
define the extent of our changes...

637
00:48:06,765 --> 00:48:10,166
and figure out how to reverse them.

638
00:48:10,268 --> 00:48:12,168
Whoa.

639
00:48:12,270 --> 00:48:14,670
<i>[ Sue ]
<i>Believe it or not, he lives here</i>

640
00:48:14,773 --> 00:48:19,142
<i>[ Reed ] But I have to warn you,</i>
<i>it's gonna be a little crowded in some areas</i>

641
00:48:19,244 --> 00:48:21,212
[Johnny Laughs ]

642
00:48:22,547 --> 00:48:26,005
So, what do you think?

643
00:48:26,117 --> 00:48:28,017
I don't know, Reed.

644
00:48:28,119 --> 00:48:31,020
I think you might be bringing
your work home with you.

645
00:48:31,122 --> 00:48:35,024
[ Laughs ] Come on. Let me show
you guys where you'll be staying.

646
00:48:35,126 --> 00:48:36,923
Busy guy.

647
00:48:37,962 --> 00:48:40,430
<i>[ Crowd Chattering ]

648
00:48:42,100 --> 00:48:43,965
- Hi, everybody.
- Mr. Von Doom!

649
00:48:44,069 --> 00:48:46,663
Would you like to comment
on the recent failure of your I.P.O.?

650
00:48:46,771 --> 00:48:48,739
<i>[ Female Reporter ]
<i>What about the rumors of a takeover?</i>

651
00:49:09,861 --> 00:49:11,988
<i>God, I was so worried about you</i>

652
00:49:12,097 --> 00:49:13,826
<i>Victor</i>

653
00:49:13,932 --> 00:49:17,834
- I'm sorry I didn't get a chance to call.
- Please.

654
00:49:17,936 --> 00:49:20,666
<i>No apologies</i>

655
00:49:20,772 --> 00:49:23,832
I've arranged for your things
to be moved to one of my condos.

656
00:49:23,942 --> 00:49:26,240
- You'll have round-the-clock care.
- Thank you.

657
00:49:26,344 --> 00:49:30,838
That's very generous of you, but I think
I should stay here with my brother...

658
00:49:30,949 --> 00:49:32,746
until we get a handle on things.

659
00:49:32,851 --> 00:49:35,581
Susan, I think you should
let my doctors have a look at you.

660
00:49:35,687 --> 00:49:37,245
<i>[ Reed ]
<i>Victor</i>

661
00:49:38,823 --> 00:49:41,291
What are you doing here?

662
00:49:41,392 --> 00:49:44,293
I'm starting to wonder
the same thing.

663
00:49:44,395 --> 00:49:48,297
- How much do you know
about what happened to you?
- Not much.

664
00:49:48,399 --> 00:49:52,460
- We need to run tests
to see the extent of the damage.
- You let me know what I can do.

665
00:49:52,570 --> 00:49:55,266
We're all in this together now.

666
00:50:03,330 --> 00:50:06,527
<i>Victor, wait</i>

667
00:50:06,633 --> 00:50:09,625
I just wanted to say I'm sorry
the mission didn't go as planned.

668
00:50:09,736 --> 00:50:12,364
Didn't go as planned?

669
00:50:12,472 --> 00:50:16,340
<i>It was a catastrophe</i>
<i>You ruined the lives of four people</i>

670
00:50:16,443 --> 00:50:19,139
With all due respect, we're both to blame.
I told you to abort.

671
00:50:19,246 --> 00:50:21,043
Abort?

672
00:50:21,147 --> 00:50:24,810
I put my company, my name,
billions of dollars on the line.

673
00:50:24,918 --> 00:50:28,046
- I will not let you make me look like a fool.
- If we could understand-

674
00:50:28,154 --> 00:50:31,282
I don't want to understand it!
This isn't one of your science projects!

675
00:50:31,391 --> 00:50:33,985
I just want to fix it, fast!

676
00:50:34,094 --> 00:50:36,722
<i>- [ Heavy Footsteps ]
<i>- [ Ben ] Is there a problem?</i>

677
00:50:40,901 --> 00:50:44,132
[ Sighs ]
No.

678
00:50:44,237 --> 00:50:46,205
- [ Bell Dings ]
- No problem, Ben.

679
00:50:46,306 --> 00:50:50,766
Just pay your damn electric bill
and get to work on finding a cure.

680
00:50:54,147 --> 00:50:55,842
[ Bell Dings ]

681
00:51:17,037 --> 00:51:19,631
Whoa!

682
00:51:19,739 --> 00:51:21,707
Wow!

683
00:51:24,711 --> 00:51:27,771
He's heating up from his core.

684
00:51:27,881 --> 00:51:29,746
<i>And his vitals are completely normal</i>

685
00:51:29,849 --> 00:51:33,080
<i>If we're going to identify</i>
<i>the source of the mutation</i>

686
00:51:33,186 --> 00:51:35,086
we need to isolate
your recombinant D.N. A... .

687
00:51:35,188 --> 00:51:37,588
So we can activate
positional genomes.

688
00:51:37,691 --> 00:51:40,057
- Huh?
- We have to do a physical
to see what got zapped.

689
00:51:40,160 --> 00:51:42,458
Oh. Why didn't you just say so?

690
00:51:42,562 --> 00:51:46,157
<i>[ Reed ]
<i>His internal organs are completely solid</i>

691
00:51:46,266 --> 00:51:48,496
[ Heart Beating ]

692
00:51:48,602 --> 00:51:52,595
How bad is it?
You know, I used to smoke.

693
00:51:52,706 --> 00:51:54,970
[ Beeping ]

694
00:51:55,075 --> 00:51:56,804
<i>[ Reed ]
<i>It's not invisibility per se</i>

695
00:51:56,910 --> 00:51:59,811
<i>You should be able to bend light</i>
<i>around other objects, even people</i>

696
00:51:59,913 --> 00:52:03,246
if you could control
your emotional state better.

697
00:52:03,350 --> 00:52:07,411
- Excuse me?
- If you had more self-control,
you could locate the trigger.

698
00:52:07,520 --> 00:52:10,489
Can you remember
your exact emotions on the bridge?

699
00:52:11,758 --> 00:52:13,658
Anger.

700
00:52:13,760 --> 00:52:16,695
Rage. Frustration.

701
00:52:16,796 --> 00:52:20,197
Okay, is there any way to duplicate
that feeling? Some memory or-

702
00:52:21,935 --> 00:52:24,335
I'm sure I can
come up with something.

703
00:52:24,437 --> 00:52:27,338
- You feel anything?
- Nope.

704
00:52:27,440 --> 00:52:29,465
Okay.

705
00:52:29,576 --> 00:52:31,544
[ Stammering ]

706
00:52:35,281 --> 00:52:37,112
It's hotter than I anticipated.

707
00:52:37,217 --> 00:52:40,015
- Johnny, back it down.
- I can go hotter!

708
00:52:40,120 --> 00:52:41,883
<i>[ Sue ]
<i>Johnny, just back it down!</i>

709
00:52:50,930 --> 00:52:53,330
[ Groans ]
Johnny, back it down right now!

710
00:52:53,433 --> 00:52:55,799
Johnny!

711
00:52:55,902 --> 00:52:57,836
- [ Alarm Buzzes ]
- Ohh!

712
00:52:57,937 --> 00:52:59,837
<i>[Johnny Laughing ]

713
00:52:59,939 --> 00:53:01,839
<i>Buzz-kill!</i>

714
00:53:01,941 --> 00:53:03,841
<i>You guys are crampin'my style!</i>

715
00:53:03,943 --> 00:53:06,468
Johnny, you were at 4,000 Kelvin.

716
00:53:06,579 --> 00:53:09,980
- Any hotter, and you're approaching supernova.
- Sweet!

717
00:53:10,083 --> 00:53:12,517
No, not sweet.
That's the temperature of the sun.

718
00:53:12,619 --> 00:53:14,519
<i>Not only could you kill yourself.</i>

719
00:53:14,621 --> 00:53:17,715
<i>But you could set fire to Earth's atmosphere</i>
<i>and destroy all human life</i>

720
00:53:17,824 --> 00:53:19,724
Got it.

721
00:53:19,826 --> 00:53:21,987
Supernova- bad.

722
00:53:28,435 --> 00:53:30,869
How's that coming?

723
00:53:35,642 --> 00:53:38,042
Oh, I'm so sorry.

724
00:53:38,144 --> 00:53:40,044
- Are you okay?
- Yeah. Fine.

725
00:53:40,146 --> 00:53:42,046
- You sure?
- Yep.

726
00:53:42,148 --> 00:53:44,048
I, um-
[ Chuckles ]

727
00:53:44,150 --> 00:53:47,551
You probably thought that was
some form of latent hostility.

728
00:53:47,654 --> 00:53:50,623
What in the world
would give me that idea?

729
00:53:54,694 --> 00:53:57,094
I mean, you broke up with me, right?

730
00:53:57,197 --> 00:53:59,631
- [ Chuckles ] Are you kidding?
<i>- No</i>

731
00:53:59,733 --> 00:54:02,361
I distinctly remember
you walked out my door, ergo-

732
00:54:02,469 --> 00:54:05,734
I was ready for the next step.
You weren't. Ergo, I walked.

733
00:54:05,839 --> 00:54:08,103
It was a little more complicated
than that.

734
00:54:08,208 --> 00:54:10,108
I just wanted
to share an apartment.

735
00:54:10,210 --> 00:54:12,576
What was so complicated about that?

736
00:54:12,679 --> 00:54:14,943
- There were a lot of variables to consider.
<i>- No, there weren't</i>

737
00:54:15,048 --> 00:54:17,175
There was you and me.

738
00:54:17,283 --> 00:54:21,379
No variables, no math.
It was actually the simplest thing in the world.

739
00:54:21,488 --> 00:54:24,389
- But like always, Reed, your head got in the way.
- No, it didn't.

740
00:54:24,491 --> 00:54:27,324
Then what was it?

741
00:54:28,862 --> 00:54:31,296
Did you feel anything when I left?

742
00:54:33,333 --> 00:54:35,893
Do you feel anything right now?

743
00:54:36,002 --> 00:54:38,061
<i>[Johnny ]
<i>Hey, guys!</i>

744
00:54:41,674 --> 00:54:44,142
I think we have a serious problem.

745
00:54:57,723 --> 00:54:59,281
Thank you.

746
00:54:59,391 --> 00:55:04,226
- How are you feeling?
- Fine. I'm good.

747
00:55:08,134 --> 00:55:10,398
Thank you for
coming out to see me.

748
00:55:10,503 --> 00:55:14,667
- You said it was urgent, so-
- It is.

749
00:55:14,774 --> 00:55:18,505
There's, uh, something
we need to talk about.

750
00:55:21,080 --> 00:55:23,048
Something I need
to ask you.

751
00:55:23,149 --> 00:55:28,883
Victor, wait a second. Um, I appreciate
everything you've done for me...

752
00:55:28,988 --> 00:55:32,253
- but I think it's a bad
idea for us to get involved.
- Just listen.

753
00:55:32,358 --> 00:55:35,885
What are you doing?

754
00:55:35,995 --> 00:55:38,623
[ Chuckles ]
I didn't bring you here...

755
00:55:38,731 --> 00:55:41,529
to talk about us.

756
00:55:41,634 --> 00:55:44,569
Please, this is business.

757
00:55:46,238 --> 00:55:49,139
[ Clears Throat ]

758
00:55:50,543 --> 00:55:54,309
I need to know, how close is Reed
to finding a cure?

759
00:55:54,413 --> 00:55:57,849
He's been working
'round the clock.

760
00:55:57,950 --> 00:56:01,579
- The data needs to be
tested and analyzed before-
- Same old Reed.

761
00:56:01,687 --> 00:56:05,282
All analysis, no action.
[ Chuckles ]

762
00:56:05,391 --> 00:56:08,087
Wasn't that the problem
with you two?

763
00:56:08,194 --> 00:56:12,631
If the molecules aren't stable, it could
make us worse- maybe even kill us.

764
00:56:12,731 --> 00:56:15,757
Then why is Reed
dragging his feet?

765
00:56:17,303 --> 00:56:21,865
Maybe he likes having
his prize specimen under a glass.

766
00:56:21,974 --> 00:56:24,135
It's ironic,
isn't it?

767
00:56:24,243 --> 00:56:28,270
You're finally the perfect woman for him
because you're his science project.

768
00:56:29,915 --> 00:56:33,180
- Please don't make this a personal matter.
- I think you already have.

769
00:56:34,587 --> 00:56:37,613
Victor, we can't do anything
until the research is ready.

770
00:56:39,692 --> 00:56:42,525
"We"?

771
00:56:44,363 --> 00:56:47,127
[ Rumbling ]

772
00:56:59,311 --> 00:57:01,871
Don't forget who
you work for, Susan.

773
00:57:01,981 --> 00:57:05,382
So get to work
and do your job.

774
00:57:33,379 --> 00:57:36,405
I wish my wife
would disappear.

775
00:57:43,856 --> 00:57:45,847
<i>[ Von Doom ]
<i>So, what's the prognosis?</i>

776
00:57:45,958 --> 00:57:50,395
<i>Your tissue, your organs, your entire</i>
<i>biophysical structure is changing</i>

777
00:57:50,496 --> 00:57:52,896
<i>Every system is still</i>
<i>functioning somehow</i>

778
00:57:52,998 --> 00:57:54,898
And it's changing into?

779
00:57:55,000 --> 00:57:59,232
I don't really know.
Some kind of organic metallic alloy.

780
00:57:59,338 --> 00:58:02,432
Stronger than titanium
or carbon steel.

781
00:58:02,541 --> 00:58:04,065
<i>Harder than diamonds</i>

782
00:58:04,176 --> 00:58:07,737
Like the shields
Reed said would protect us.

783
00:58:09,048 --> 00:58:10,982
[ Exhales ]

784
00:58:11,083 --> 00:58:13,502
How long?

785
00:58:14,435 --> 00:58:16,733
At this rate, the infection could be
complete in two, maybe three weeks.

786
00:58:16,838 --> 00:58:18,738
What do you mean, complete?

787
00:58:18,840 --> 00:58:20,740
I wish I could tell you.

788
00:58:20,842 --> 00:58:24,243
I can't pretend to know
what we're dealing with here.

789
00:58:24,345 --> 00:58:26,939
- I'll have to notify the C.D.C.
- What?

790
00:58:27,048 --> 00:58:29,676
<i>- The Center for Disease Control</i>
- I know what it is.

791
00:58:29,784 --> 00:58:33,083
If this thing is contagious,
we may have a big problem on our hands.

792
00:58:33,187 --> 00:58:35,485
<i>I'm talking about an epidemic here</i>

793
00:58:35,590 --> 00:58:37,558
[ Laughs ]
Look at me.

794
00:58:39,494 --> 00:58:43,863
I have a life. I'm the... face
of a billion-dollar company.

795
00:58:45,566 --> 00:58:48,057
We need to keep this confidential.

796
00:58:48,169 --> 00:58:51,935
Victor, this disease is progressive,
degenerative. I have to notify someone.

797
00:58:52,040 --> 00:58:54,736
- [ Choking ]
- That's terrible news.

798
00:59:02,583 --> 00:59:05,552
I think I'll get a second opinion.

799
00:59:34,315 --> 00:59:37,580
<i>Our uniforms were exposed</i>
<i>to the storm, like us</i>

800
00:59:37,685 --> 00:59:39,585
so they can transform like us...

801
00:59:39,687 --> 00:59:42,815
becoming invisible, changing size on demand
or remaining impervious to flame.

802
00:59:42,924 --> 00:59:45,586
You guys look like an '80s rock band.
[ Laughing ]

803
00:59:45,693 --> 00:59:47,558
You know, Ben,
this material stretches.

804
00:59:47,662 --> 00:59:50,460
- I'm sure I can figure out a way to make it fit.
- [ Stammers ]

805
00:59:50,565 --> 00:59:52,465
I wouldn't be caught dead
wearing that.

806
00:59:52,567 --> 00:59:55,468
I love these costumes! They're missing
something, though. Needs, like, spice-

807
00:59:55,570 --> 00:59:59,028
- They're not costumes.
- You can't use your powers in public, Johnny.

808
00:59:59,140 --> 01:00:01,199
You guys are worse than NASA.

809
01:00:01,309 --> 01:00:03,209
<i>[ Sue ]
<i>Johnny-[ Scoffs ]

810
01:00:03,311 --> 01:00:04,972
Maybe it's missing a utility belt.
[ Chuckling ]

811
01:00:06,364 --> 01:00:09,595
If we can build a machine to recreate
the storm, we can reverse the polarity.

812
01:00:09,700 --> 01:00:13,295
- And reverse the mutations.
- Curing countless diseases, not just ours.

813
01:00:13,404 --> 01:00:15,372
But we're the focus,
right, Reed?

814
01:00:15,473 --> 01:00:18,636
<i>- Reed?</i>
- Yeah, of course. Of course.

815
01:00:18,743 --> 01:00:21,507
<i>And you're sure you can</i>
<i>control this thing?</i>

816
01:00:21,612 --> 01:00:24,103
- Because last time it didn't work out so well.
- With the right amount...

817
01:00:24,215 --> 01:00:26,115
of energy we can stabilize
the storm.

818
01:00:26,217 --> 01:00:29,209
Maybe tie in
to the city grid.

819
01:00:33,157 --> 01:00:35,625
You know, you really
need a janitor.

820
01:00:37,094 --> 01:00:40,791
I bet this is what it looks like
inside your head.

821
01:00:44,602 --> 01:00:46,968
- Oh!
- Sue!

822
01:00:58,682 --> 01:01:00,707
[ Chuckles ]

823
01:01:01,852 --> 01:01:04,412
<i>- [ Sue Chuckles ]
<i>- [ Reed ] That's okay</i>

824
01:01:04,522 --> 01:01:06,922
- My fault.
- No problem.

825
01:01:08,426 --> 01:01:12,055
- Hi.
- Hi.

826
01:01:12,163 --> 01:01:15,030
<i>[ Doors Close ]

827
01:01:15,132 --> 01:01:18,397
<i>[ Elevator Gears Whir ]

828
01:01:18,502 --> 01:01:22,495
- Did it just get really hot in here?
- Yeah. It-Yeah.

829
01:01:22,606 --> 01:01:25,973
It's weird.

830
01:01:26,076 --> 01:01:28,738
Yeah, it's-Whoo.

831
01:01:28,846 --> 01:01:31,212
Whoo!

832
01:01:31,315 --> 01:01:36,014
- Is this your floor?
- No. I was gonna- It's broken or somethin'.

833
01:01:36,120 --> 01:01:38,918
- You guys goin' up?
- Is it hot in here?

834
01:01:39,023 --> 01:01:41,184
Yes.

835
01:01:42,426 --> 01:01:44,394
Listen, I'll call you
about that drink, okay?

836
01:01:44,495 --> 01:01:47,055
- Good-bye.
- Bye-bye.

837
01:01:48,899 --> 01:01:51,163
I'll talk to you later.
Bye.

838
01:01:51,268 --> 01:01:54,567
[ Sighs ]
It's like a sauna in here.

839
01:01:54,672 --> 01:01:57,004
It's been like this
all day.

840
01:02:02,580 --> 01:02:04,707
<i>There you go</i>
<i>There's your change</i>

841
01:02:05,850 --> 01:02:07,750
<i>Can I help you, buddy?</i>

842
01:02:07,852 --> 01:02:09,581
- Oh, my-
<i>- It's Sue Storm!</i>

843
01:02:09,687 --> 01:02:11,917
- It's the Invisible Woman!
<i>- Hey, you're right!</i>

844
01:02:12,022 --> 01:02:15,549
<i>Sue Storm! It</i> is <i>you!</i>
<i>Listen, my kid loves you!</i>

845
01:02:15,659 --> 01:02:19,026
[ Shouting, Chattering ]

846
01:02:22,500 --> 01:02:24,627
I can't believe
I'm doing this again!

847
01:02:38,933 --> 01:02:42,664
All right, I'm here. Let's make this quick.
I got places to go today.

848
01:02:42,770 --> 01:02:45,534
- [ Grumbles ]
- Oh, wait. [ Laughs ] I don't go anywhere.

849
01:02:45,639 --> 01:02:49,803
Johnny, it's imperative that we
stay inside for the foreseeable future.

850
01:02:49,910 --> 01:02:52,504
<i>I know, I know, Reed, but when you</i>
<i>said that last time my brain hurt a week</i>

851
01:02:52,613 --> 01:02:54,672
Johnny, it's too dangerous
for you to be in public.

852
01:02:54,782 --> 01:02:56,579
You've been saying that for years.

853
01:02:56,684 --> 01:02:59,482
What worries me
is that our powers are evolving.

854
01:02:59,587 --> 01:03:03,751
<i>I know I know!
<i>I am so close to flying, guys, I can taste it</i>

855
01:03:03,858 --> 01:03:06,156
- You can't fly.
- Yet.

856
01:03:06,260 --> 01:03:09,821
- Johnny, can you put that napkin out?
- Oh, Jesus.

857
01:03:10,931 --> 01:03:13,525
What's going on?
How you gonna cure us?

858
01:03:13,634 --> 01:03:17,195
I'm gonna build a machine
to re-create the storm.

859
01:03:17,304 --> 01:03:20,740
<i>The cosmic rays will travel</i>
<i>from this generator to this chamber</i>

860
01:03:20,841 --> 01:03:22,741
<i>What, no pop-ups?</i>

861
01:03:22,843 --> 01:03:25,175
<i>If I can reverse the wave signal-</i>

862
01:03:25,279 --> 01:03:28,009
It'll return us back to normal.

863
01:03:28,115 --> 01:03:31,846
- Huh.
<i>- Right But what are the risks?</i>

864
01:03:31,952 --> 01:03:35,046
Even a small miscalculation could
increase our symptoms exponentially.

865
01:03:35,156 --> 01:03:37,784
- [ Metal Crunches ]
- Or perhaps even kill us.

866
01:03:37,892 --> 01:03:40,383
<i>Now, dying- that's bad, right?</i>

867
01:03:40,494 --> 01:03:43,395
<i>I say wejust let sleeping dogs lie, guys</i>

868
01:03:43,497 --> 01:03:46,466
- So, how long till this
contraption's up and runnin'?
- It's hard to say.

869
01:03:46,567 --> 01:03:48,694
- How long, Reed?
- I don't know-

870
01:03:48,802 --> 01:03:50,736
<i>You don't</i> know?

871
01:03:50,838 --> 01:03:52,897
- You don't want this to get worse.
- Worse than <i>that?</i>

872
01:03:53,007 --> 01:03:55,737
<i>Guys, look, we're gonna</i>
<i>be stuck here for a while</i>

873
01:03:55,843 --> 01:03:58,744
<i>So let's just try and get along</i>

874
01:03:58,846 --> 01:04:01,314
<i>##[ Rock ]

875
01:04:03,317 --> 01:04:06,286
<i>##[ Man Vocalizing ]

876
01:04:12,560 --> 01:04:14,460
- Ohh!
- You could knock!

877
01:04:14,562 --> 01:04:16,086
Sorry!

878
01:04:20,768 --> 01:04:23,498
<i>##[ Continues ]

879
01:04:45,226 --> 01:04:47,194
<i>##[ Ends ]

880
01:04:50,397 --> 01:04:52,831
Johnny!

